Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.66,0:00:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the rhythm of the wind, deductions become clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.29,0:00:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figuring out the secret trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.42,0:00:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The seven tiered festival doll set.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.09,0:00:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the mystery of the robber who stole it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.46,0:00:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that one truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.34,0:00:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.76,0:00:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.02,0:01:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, look! That empress!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.65,0:01:52.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.48,0:01:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:56.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right, Girls' Day is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:59.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Girls Day, or Hinamatsuri, is celebrated on March 3rd, where girls set up dolls in a certain order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.66,0:02:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be nice... That empress...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.87,0:02:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Ayumi, don't you already own one?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.83,0:02:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, did you forget already?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.42,0:02:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last year, you dropped it and its hand and neck fell off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.30,0:02:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gah, th-that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.96,0:02:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry, Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.68,0:02:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, couldn't you have had it repaired?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.76,0:02:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.72,0:02:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, while it was being repaired, an artisan cut himself and got blood on the doll's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.14,0:02:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, when we finally thought it was fixed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the neighbor's dog, Peach, came up to Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} holding the broken doll's neck in its jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.20,0:02:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paint that was hiding the blood had come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.41,0:02:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doll's hair was untidy, and it was looking at her with a dreadful glare...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.16,0:02:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.75,0:02:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That doll is definitely cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.08,0:02:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.46,0:03:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s father personally put those evil festival dolls in a box in a locked storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.76,0:03:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even now, they're deep down in the storage room... still asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.90,0:03:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Peach just wanted to hurry and show me the doll...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:24.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, the neck accidentally came off...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.91,0:03:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.91,0:03:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.74,0:03:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.21,0:03:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.96,0:03:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Uncle that owned Peach felt bad, so he asked an acquaintance to let me have their old festival dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.30,0:03:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's bigger than my old one, a seven tiered set!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.06,0:03:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can memorize how to set up the dolls, I can have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.81,0:03:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But did you say seven rows? There must be a lot of dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you be okay on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.48,0:04:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine! I tried my best to memorize it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.65,0:04:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, I won't be on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.41,0:04:16.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Festival Dolls Dyed in the Setting Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.08,0:04:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, do you remember the arrangement? Last time, I wasn't sure if you could do it, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.55,0:04:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, 111 be okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.59,0:04:30.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Well! Then, let's begin the set-up right away, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.55,0:04:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Housewife
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.81,0:04:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This many boxes are filled with dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.60,0:04:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why do you have to memorize the whole arrangement?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.90,0:04:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thinks Ayumi is going to mess u
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She doesn't really want to give away the dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.69,0:04:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:51.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ItÂ£s to make sure the child fully understands how valuable the dolls actually are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.33,0:04:57.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Once you remember the arrangement, you will grow more attached to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.54,0:04:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.16,0:05:02.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Those are special, precious dolls that I went out and bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it your best, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.18,0:05:08.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.68,0:05:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.81,0:05:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, that's wrong! The Archer is further up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.23,0:05:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.06,0:05:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wouldn't it be better if things were more lively?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.03,0:05:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has to be done right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.07,0:05:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That old man there is the Minister of the Left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.20,0:05:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's placed on the fourth row on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.20,0:05:35.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The similar one in the red is the Minister of the Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.79,0:05:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's placed on the same row, but on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.00,0:05:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Left on right and right on left?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.59,0:05:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure know a lot about this, for a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.30,0:05:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, I remember helping Ran with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.89,0:05:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you did this too, when you were a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.23,0:06:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sent to study abroad in America at a very young age,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:06.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so this is the first time I've ever touched a festival doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.07,0:06:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My parents bought my sister some that looked like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.53,0:06:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, soon after my birth, they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These dolls would bring back painful memories of them, so my sister put them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.88,0:06:27.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, how did your parents die?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.05,0:06:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. My sister was told it was due to an accident during research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Pisco said that your parents were scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.31,0:06:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, my mother wasn't very well-known,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but my father, Miyano Atsushi became infamous for his research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.86,0:06:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An outcast in the world, they called him "Mad Scientist."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.03,0:06:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mad Scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:07:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you inherit your parent's research on that drug?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that drug supposed to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.75,0:07:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A secret nostrum to raise the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that answer satisfactory?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.26,0:07:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-Then, could it be... That what he wrote in his diary was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.14,0:07:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other day, that article you saw on the computer led you to their whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.94,0:07:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you followed their scent, eventually finding their location.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But something went wrong while you were waiting in the coin locker, and you lost them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.20,0:07:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's pretty much it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.49,0:07:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Y-yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.53,0:07:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you can relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.04,0:07:45.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The purpose of my research wasn't to create a crazy drug like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most people in this world wouldn't see the benefit of something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.38,0:07:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how the little girls in this country are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who appreciate those festival dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.31,0:08:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... First there's the Emperor and the Empress,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.94,0:08:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the Three Court Ladies, the Five Male Musicians, and the Minister of Left and Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.65,0:08:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, to finish it off, here we have the Merry Drinker, the Maudlin Drinker, and the Cantankerous Drinker!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.29,0:08:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You passed it perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.79,0:08:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then can I actually have all of these festival dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't forget to thank Grandma later!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's start putting them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why so soon after we just set them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.01,0:08:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no choice. We have to clean them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait! I want to take a picture of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.06,0:08:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I brought my dad's digital camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.86,0:08:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say Cheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.53,0:09:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.99,0:09:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from room 503...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.83,0:09:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's about that again, my husband should have already declined...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.46,0:09:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'm aware of that, but I can't let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:21.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Today I brought an appraiser with me, and I would like to have another discussion with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.14,0:09:23.39,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:31.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are some splendid festival dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think they were made by a famous artisan in Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.15,0:09:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, have you made up your mind about whether you'll sell or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.99,0:09:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to buy these festival dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.20,0:09:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're too late, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.99,0:09:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These now belong to Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No, I don't have any daughters, and I'm not interested in dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I want to buy is that scroll behind you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.55,0:10:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the Thunder God, painted in the Edo Period by Tetsuzan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.55,0:10:00.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Edo Period, or Tokugawa Period, ran from 1603 to 1868.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already own the pair of this, the scroll of the Wind God, and I really want to own both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.18,0:10:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, my husband says it isn't for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.19,0:10:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, there's no way it's worth so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.61,0:10:16.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't even know the estimated price of this scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.98,0:10:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how much insurance credit your late father-in-law had to take to buy this scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.37,0:10:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2-20 million yen, 20 million!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That much?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.37,0:10:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told your husband I'd be willing to pay double that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, ma'am, it's such a pity for the scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.55,0:10:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way it's stored here, it will lose its value.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.97,0:10:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be wise to sell it to a professional collector like Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But, my husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.51,0:10:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.18,0:10:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not for any price...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.81,0:10:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll come back tonight when your husband gets home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.99,0:11:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I'll be able to change your husband's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.95,0:11:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once I mention about his stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.37,0:11:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-Then, well pack up the festival dolls and leave too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So many memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.05,0:11:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last time I took these out must have been 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.63,0:11:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that they're finally out in the open. I'm sure that the dolls are delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.22,0:11:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, is it okay if the dolls stay here until the end of Girls' Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then my Mother can take a last look at the dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.07,0:11:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.74,0:11:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, can we stay here for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.07,0:11:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to take one more photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then my mother^could make some sweet sake for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:56.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sweet sake is a traditional, sweet, non-alcoholic Japanese drink made from fermented rice, sake lees being one of the ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.83,0:11:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Setsuko;san, I think we're out of sake lees.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.12,0:11:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, how bothersome...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:12:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I need to leave soon too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we can go get some! The supermarket isn't very far!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.35,0:12:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, tell us already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of photo do you want to take?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One that shows our friendship!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we just take one like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.94,0:12:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This will be an even better one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.24,0:12:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, which way?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.95,0:12:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.99,0:12:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, just a bit longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.87,0:12:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's around this corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.25,0:12:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the Appraiser Uncle from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.51,0:12:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.59,0:12:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-W-Well, I seem to have lost my cell phone somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.85,0:12:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I dialed my number, the grandmother answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.89,0:12:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said it's in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:12:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me to get it when I come back this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.65,0:13:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I might get an important call, so I came back right away to get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.24,0:13:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like nobody's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.28,0:13:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The grandmother wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. Nobody's answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.62,0:13:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody's answering...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:26.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how come the door isn't locked?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.38,0:13:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandma, are you sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.06,0:13:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a fax machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's coming from that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.11,0:13:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What the heck happened in this room!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like a fax from the husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.62,0:13:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.87,0:13:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the only place that looks like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.66,0:14:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was robbers! While we were gone, robbers must have broken in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.09,0:14:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They might have also been in the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.47,0:14:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness! It looks like the Empress is okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.72,0:14:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like this room was left undamaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, where did the grandma go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.02,0:14:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the grandmother isn't the only thing that's missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look. The scroll of the Thunder God is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.33,0:14:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to contact the police! Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.33,0:14:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.08,0:14:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.46,0:14:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I knew that I heard all of you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you, Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.30,0:14:55.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just went out to the store to buy some sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.05,0:15:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with that put aside, why does everyone look so frightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.31,0:15:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Setsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't you have some errands to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.02,0:15:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I forgot my purse here when I left, and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, I was just about to go call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.74,0:15:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsu-Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.12,0:15:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What just happened? I heard a scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.38,0:15:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's talk about it when the police arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.76,0:15:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So this is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.18,0:15:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kids arrived here to set up the festival dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.10,0:15:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bit later, trying to pressure them into selling the scroll, Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived with the appraiser Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.82,0:15:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Officer, please don't put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.57,0:15:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after both of them left, all five of you went grocery shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.49,0:16:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, to buy sake lees!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.79,0:16:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sake lees?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.33,0:16:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My mother,was going to prepare some sweet sake, but we ran out of ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had an errand to run, the children offered to go buy some.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, after that, you were home all alone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.51,0:16:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, did you notice anything strange? Like an odd sound...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.27,0:16:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.31,0:16:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the cell phone this person forgot rang in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.65,0:16:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your cell phone in the living room...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We passed through the living room first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.24,0:16:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard that there were kids in the tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.53,0:16:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we wanted to hurry and see the hanging scroll, so we went into the tatami room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after you received the phone call, why did you leave the building?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.71,0:16:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To buy sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.59,0:16:59.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were all out of sugar, so I quickly went out to get some.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.80,0:17:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, do you know what time it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It was right after I had the phone conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, then I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.15,0:17:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before I hung up the phone, I heard the sound of the fax machine starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.49,0:17:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All fax documents have the time and date they were sent on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So who sent that fax?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.08,0:17:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could you show me where this fax is?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.08,0:17:29.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.50,0:17:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa. This room is a complete mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.84,0:17:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be the fax from your husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.13,0:17:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,3:28 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was anything else stolen besides the scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.85,0:17:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all of the rooms besides this one and the bedroom were left alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.98,0:17:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the purse I left on the cabinet above the TV in the bedroom wasn't taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.78,0:17:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.86,0:18:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the burglar entered through this route using the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.29,0:18:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could this be used as the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.79,0:18:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the 6th floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.54,0:18:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robbers can make use of the area, and use a rope to get down from the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.34,0:18:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higher floors tend to be robbed because wealthy people usually live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.34,0:18:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People think it's safe and leave their balcony doors unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.22,0:18:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.76,0:18:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I live with a grandfather who loves entertainment news.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys first realized the house had been robbed when you entered this room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.81,0:18:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when we came back here, we found the door was unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:43.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard the sound of the fax machine from the living room, and found that everything was thrown around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.82,0:18:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that happened, the time on the fax was 15:40 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.95,0:18:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the robbery took place sometime between 3:30 and 3:40 PM, giving them ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.29,0:18:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.54,0:19:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber entered into the house by using the balcony, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.97,0:19:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I were him, I would be afraid to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.55,0:19:11.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, if the curtains are closed you wouldn't be able to see the inside from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.98,0:19:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they opened the door to look inside the room, the wind would blow the curtain up and the grandmother would see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.11,0:19:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.40,0:19:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time on all of these faxes is 3:28 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, before we arrived back here, the fax was running the whole time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.87,0:19:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would a burglar enter a room that's always receiving messages, and risk being caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.54,0:19:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they wouldn't be scared of a fax machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of the fax machine that they're scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.13,0:19:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will notify when it finishes receiving a message, and usually somebody will come and check the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.51,0:19:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, a normal burglar wouldn't just leave the purse lying in the open in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.98,0:19:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after looking in the bedroom, why didn't they look through all of the other rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.86,0:20:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-True...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.73,0:20:07.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the strangest thing is... why did they only take the scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.24,0:20:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the scroll is worth 20 million yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.37,0:20:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you'd have to be a professional to know how much it's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.08,0:20:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the burglar knew from the beginning that the scroll was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.67,0:20:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.17,0:20:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except if they only wanted to take the scroll, they wouldn't need to go through the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.35,0:20:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They went through the bedroom to create a crime scene, and mislead the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.06,0:20:42.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the culprit doesn't have an alibi, and knew they would have to talk to the police about the case at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.03,0:20:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, that person has to know how much the hanging scroll is worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.70,0:20:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, weren't you lurking around the house before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.62,0:20:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Now, what are you saying? I was looking for my cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.00,0:20:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the door was unlocked!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.33,0:21:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.71,0:21:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you lock the door when you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I think I locked the door... But I'm not entirely sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Uncle, why were you in front of the house earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't return for a while, so I came here to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two were with each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.60,0:21:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.52,0:21:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you knew that Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had forgotten his cell phone here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.19,0:21:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was next to me right until I called and started talking to the grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.12,0:21:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You left while he was on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.12,0:21:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-To buy cigarettes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.20,0:21:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, just like he said, neither of you two have solid alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.13,0:21:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey! You can't just suspect both of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.13,0:21:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two receive 20 million yen in insurance money if the scroll is stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.93,0:21:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that either one of you two could have done it as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.52,0:21:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.98,0:22:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.98,0:22:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, this is quite difficult...
